This paper deals with the topic of anonymity in peer-to-peer systems, which is a common concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). It also involves the use of anonymity relays, which falls under the category of network security (cs.NI). The proposed modification for BitTorrent involves creating a marketplace for trading in k swarms, which could be considered a distributed computing system (cs.DC) or a system for information exchange (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents simulation results and analyzes the effectiveness of the proposed system, which could be seen as a data analysis or machine learning problem (cs.DS).
